    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18) anchoring the lineup, representing our highest-upside plays. **Kyle Tucker** benefits tremendously from a premium matchup against Feltner, capitalizing on a significant park factor (+14%) and favorable SP skill data to reach the daily ceiling. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start not only for his elite base projections but for the tactical advantage provided by his leadoff spot against Williams, G; despite the slight deduction for the opposing pitcher\u2019s 53% hold rate on the basepaths, **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s plate appearance volume makes him the cornerstone of our offensive strategy. Both players are supported by **Andy Pages** (75.64), who draws a similar favorable environment against Feltner, with the added bonus of a slow pitcher delivery that bolsters his stolen base probability.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved keeping **Nasim Nunez** (60.21) on the bench. While his score is respectable, **Nasim Nunez** fell just short of displacing our lower-tier starters due to a combination of a lower batting order position and negative efficiency modifiers tied to the catcher\u2019s pop time. We are prioritizing the higher ceiling of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and the volume of **Josh Lowe** (72.21), the latter of whom is a critical asset today due to the combination of a weak opposing starter in M\u00e1rquez (5.26 xERA) and the potential for a green light on the basepaths. We continue to monitor the status of **Marcell Ozuna** and **Heliot Ramos**, but with the current lineup producing solid efficiency scores, they remain on the bench to preserve our limited game caps for more optimal platoon alignments later in the week.\n\nRisks remain focused on the lower end of our outfield depth, specifically **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.07) and **Jackson Merrill** (56.12). Both players face marginal-to-tough SP skill matchups that suppress their potential; **Luis Robert Jr.** in particular is dealing with a significant platoon penalty (-15%), making him our most volatile start. While these players sit near the 60-point threshold, they are active only because the current data on **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Jung** (not pictured in today\u2019s active field) necessitates keeping our high-floor core intact. Owners should track weather reports for the matchups involving **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Miguel Vargas**, as any sudden shifts in wind patterns could tighten the margins for these middle-order hitters.",
